  "body": "(I'm not really sure if they are called escape characters in this case, but you get the idea.)\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhardhat node > log.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then send a couple of repeated RPC calls, for example doing\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST --data \\\r\n        '{\"id\":1337,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_blockNumber\",\"params\":[]}' \\\r\n        http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\ntwice.\r\n\r\nResult:\r\n\r\n```\r\neth_blockNumber\r\n\u001B[?25l\u001B[Feth_blockNumber (2)\r\n\u001B[K\u001B[?25h\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think a `if (process.stdout.isTTY)` check somewhere should fix this.",
